				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: About Bard CC<a name="33225"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 4:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If this was a hard level LDON, then lull gets resisted about 75% of the time, more or less.  If the bard doesn't have an especially high charisma, a lot of times when lull is resisted, it will agro the mob (and of course any mobs nearby).  Mez is not terribly hard to land on hard LDON mobs, but if you have two or three beating on you, you can easily die before you get them all mezzed.  There are definite tricks and techniques beyond basic pacification and crowd control that you have to use to successfully pull a hard LDON.  If he was new to pulling hard level, well -- I'm not bad at it, but I lost the first couple of tries and died quite often in the process of learning.
<br />

<br />
So if he was new to doing hard level, then what you describe makes sense.  If you were not doing hard, well, then it sounds like this bard was rather pathetic.</span></td>
