				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: About Bard CC<a name="33398"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 04 2:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't think the Bard was Ebayed.  Probably just not a very good player.
<br />

<br />
As for Lulling and pulling, the Takish dungeons have the worst aggro for pulling of all the ones I have done.  LOTS of aggro through doors and walls etc.  As someone else mentioned, if it was a Hard dungeon, then Lulling pretty much sucks, and you WILL get multiple pulls.
<br />

<br />
If the Bard was lower than most in the group, it could also be that his mez or charm was resisted a lot.  In fact, there are gaps in what level mobs we can mez and charm, based on what level we are and what level the mobs are.  For example, our lvl 53 Mez song only works on mobs up to lvl 55.  Our next mez upgrade is at lvl 58, and only works on mobs up to lvl 57.  Basically, for much of a Bard's life, they can only mez dark blue mobs.  Even cons, yellows, or reds are often simply not possible.
<br />

<br />
Now, the bard being &quot;upset that he had to pull&quot; tells me that the guy probably isn't very skilled.  My GF plays a bard.  It is her first toon.  Before she played EQ, her favorite game was Tetris.  You see where I'm going with this.  She avoids LDoNs, and only goes with me or another Bard she knows, because she dreads all the responsibility that goes with Pulling and CC.  She does not want to be the reason a group wipes.  She is getting better all the time.  She uses charm a lot when she solos, and is getting the mechanics of toggling targets etc.  But doing group CC is challenging, and she knows it.  (That of course, is why most of us like being Bards, hehe.)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
