				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: About Bard CC<a name="34028"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 11 04 9:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First off, that's not a bad group composition for Guk at all and especially good if the last member was a SK or Pal.  Having a necro in Guk is quite useful for the reasons you mentioned and also because the pet (or BST pet) can off tank a mob and allow the bard to get things under control (assuming he can target in Guk, which remains a problem).
<br />

<br />
Deepest Guk, with it's hidden mobs and changes of elevation, presents a real challenge to one who isn't familiar with pulling it.  I recall partially wiping my first two groups as I learned the eccentricities of pulling this dungeon.  There are some tricks to pulling Guk and asking those who have done so successfully is a good way of learning with minimal pain.
<br />

<br />
If the bard was not using bind sight or an &quot;eye&quot;/stalking probe, it's almost a guarantee that on his first few attempts,  he will pull 3-4 at a time.  Once deftdance is burned, he has to rely upon having enough AC and avoidance to get off the mezzes while the mobs are attacking.  If he doesn't have the AC, HP and avoidance, success is problematic.
<br />

<br />
If a bard is &quot;very, very upset&quot; with the prospect of pulling, then that player simply isn't comfortable with the bard's role as puller or already has had bad experiences in Guk.   That could be because he's new to the class (purchased), has been soloing his previous levels, has failed on previous attempts to pull the theme, or is simply not a very good bard.  
<br />

<br />
Moreover, if a bard or monk doesn't <i>want</i> to pull, it's probably not a good idea to force the issue.  Lacking skill or desire to pull in Guk could make for some fairly eventful missions, even on normal.
<br />

<br />
Without knowing the level of the bard, it's hard to analyze the lack of crowd control (i.e., mezzing) beyond what I've already stated.
<br />

<br />
On normal level, SSoQ works well, but pulling singles constantly is quite difficult with the current targeting problems.  Pulling two is the norm (three some times) and mezzing them from the off-tank(s) follows.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
