				<td colspan="2"><span>At level 49 my first pulling for an LDON was in a TAK dungeon (this was my 3rd LDON overall).  I was the lowest member of the group, and after about 3 of 5 pulls bringing multiples and then opening a door brought a room down on our group, the Pally started pulling and we managed to win the collect with about 3 min to spare.
<br />

<br />
Fast forward a few levels, about 10 LDON's pulled and a few nights ago I pulled for a group of 5 in TAK and only got adds twice, and that was just 1 extra I mezzed easily.  We finished the collect with lots of time to spare.
<br />

<br />
So, I concur with the comments mentioned above.  The bard in your group was probably very inexperienced in pulling and/or had bad experiences in TAK previous.  There is really no reason in a normal with a decent charisma and some exp in TAK dungeons to have those problems, although I have seen comments from some on one particular TAK dungeon layout that is hard to pull.
<br />

<br />
Badji
<br />
Minstril on ARO
